  "text": "We note that so far we have assumed that z is a feature output in F , i.e., z = x (k) for some k ∈ [K]. However, the above treatment would stay the same if z is the concatenation of multiple feature outputs. One can also obtain a separate sample entropy term for separate feature outputs and add them to the objective in [CITATION_1] .",
